oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Barnsite to be leveled
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Clement, William L., photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Before picture of area to be graded for erection of livestock sale barn for the Mid-State Livestock Producer's Association. Work is just now starting on cutting and leveling hilltop for barn. Located three miles east of Woodbury.

One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil Conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s.
